      <title class="- topic/title ">
         <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">12.102</ph> Applicability.</title>
      <conbody class="- topic/body  concept/conbody ">
         <ol id="d678e13" class="- topic/ol ">
            <li class="- topic/li ">
               <p id="d705e10" class="- topic/p ">
                  <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(a)</ph> This part shall be used for the
acquisition of supplies or services that meet <ph rev="FAC 2022-01 December 6, 2021" class="- topic/ph "><?FM MARKER [CaseNumber] FAR Case 2018-018?>the definitions of “commercial
product” or “commercial service”<?FM MARKER [Why] Amend section 12.102 by—
a. Removing from paragraph (a) the phrase “the definition of commercial items” and adding “the definitions of “commercial product” or “commercial service” in its place;?></ph> at <xref href="2.101.dita#FAR_2_101"
                        base="i1125359"
                        outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly"
                        class="- topic/xref ">2.101</xref>.</p>
            </li>
            <li class="- topic/li ">
               <p id="d705e23" class="- topic/p ">
                  <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(b)</ph> Contracting
officers shall use the policies in this part in conjunction with
the policies and procedures for solicitation, evaluation and award
prescribed in <xref href="Part_13.dita#FAR_Part_13"
                        base="i1112458"
                        outputclass="fm:Part"
                        class="- topic/xref ">part  13</xref>, Simplified
Acquisition Procedures; <xref href="Part_14.dita#FAR_Part_14"
                        base="i1111055"
                        outputclass="fm:Part"
                        class="- topic/xref ">part  14</xref>,
Sealed Bidding; or <xref href="Part_15.dita#FAR_Part_15"
                        base="i1109360"
                        outputclass="fm:Part"
                        class="- topic/xref ">part  15</xref>,
Contracting by Negotiation, as appropriate for the particular acquisition.</p>
            </li>
            <li class="- topic/li ">
               <p id="d705e37" class="- topic/p ">
                  <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(c)</ph> Contracts
for the acquisition of <ph rev="FAC 2022-01 December 6, 2021" class="- topic/ph "><?FM MARKER [CaseNumber] FAR Case 2018-018?>commercial
products or commercial services<?FM MARKER [Why] b.Removing from paragraph (c) the term “commercial items” wherever it appears and adding “commercial products or commercial services” in its place;?></ph> are subject to the policies
in other parts of the FAR. When a policy in another part of the
FAR is inconsistent with a policy in this part, this <xref href="Part_12.dita#FAR_Part_12"
                        base="i1113784"
                        outputclass="fm:Part"
                        class="- topic/xref ">part  12</xref> shall take
precedence for the acquisition of <ph rev="FAC 2022-01 December 6, 2021" class="- topic/ph ">commercial products or
commercial services.</ph>
               </p>
            </li>
            <li class="- topic/li ">
               <p id="d705e52" class="- topic/p ">
                  <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(d)</ph> The definition
of <ph rev="FAC 2022-01 December 6, 2021" class="- topic/ph "><?FM MARKER [CaseNumber] FAR Case 2018-018?>commercial product<?FM MARKER [Why] c. Removing from paragraph (d) the phrase “commercial item in section 2.101” and adding “commercial product” in its place;c.Removing from paragraph (d) the phrase “commercial item in section 2.101” and adding “commercial product” in its place;?></ph> uses
the phrase “purposes other than governmental purposes”. These purposes are
those that are not unique to a government.</p>
            </li>
            <li class="- topic/li ">
               <p id="d705e62" class="- topic/p ">
                  <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(e)</ph> This part
shall not apply to the acquisition of <ph rev="FAC 2022-01 December 6, 2021" class="- topic/ph "><?FM MARKER [CaseNumber] FAR Case 2018-018?>commercial products or
commercial services—<?FM MARKER [Why] d. Removing from paragraphs (e) and (f)(1) the term “commercial items” and adding “commercial products or commercial services” in its place;?></ph>
               </p>
               <ol id="d678e77" class="- topic/ol ">
                  <li class="- topic/li ">
                     <p id="d705e72" class="- topic/p ">
                        <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(1)</ph> At or below the micro-purchase
threshold;</p>
                  </li>
                  <li class="- topic/li ">
                     <p id="d705e77" class="- topic/p ">
                        <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(2)</ph> Using the <xref href="https://www.gsa.gov/forms-library/us-government-purchase-order-invoice-voucher"
                              format="html"
                              scope="external"
                              class="- topic/xref ">Standard Form 44</xref> (see <xref href="13.306.dita#FAR_13_306"
                              base="i1111753"
                              outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly"
                              class="- topic/xref ">13.306</xref>);</p>
                  </li>
                  <li class="- topic/li ">
                     <p id="d705e88" class="- topic/p ">
                        <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(3)</ph> Using the
imprest fund (see <xref href="13.305.dita#FAR_13_305"
                              base="i1111714"
                              outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly"
                              class="- topic/xref ">13.305</xref>);</p>
                  </li>
                  <li class="- topic/li ">
                     <p id="d705e96" class="- topic/p ">
                        <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(4)</ph> Using the
Governmentwide commercial purchase card as a method of purchase
rather than only as a method of payment; or</p>
                  </li>
                  <li class="- topic/li ">
                     <p id="d705e101" class="- topic/p ">
                        <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(5)</ph> Directly
from another Federal agency.</p>
                  </li>
               </ol>
            </li>
            <li props="Runin" class="- topic/li ">
               <p id="d705e106" class="- topic/p ">
                  <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(f)</ph>
               </p>
               <ol id="d678e144" class="- topic/ol ">
                  <li class="- topic/li ">
                     <p id="d705e111" class="- topic/p ">
                        <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(1)</ph> Contracting
officers may treat any acquisition of supplies or services that,
as determined by the head of the agency, are to be used to facilitate
defense against or recovery from cyber, nuclear, biological, chemical,
or radiological attack, as an acquisition of <ph rev="FAC 2022-01 December 6, 2021" class="- topic/ph "><?FM MARKER [CaseNumber] FAR Case 2018-018?>commercial products or
commercial services.<?FM MARKER [Why] d. Removing from paragraphs (e) and (f)(1) the term “commercial items” and adding “commercial products or commercial services” in its place;?></ph>
                     </p>
                  </li>
                  <li class="- topic/li ">
                     <p id="d705e120" class="- topic/p ">
                        <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(2)</ph> A contract
in an amount greater than $20 million that is awarded on a sole
source basis<ph rev="FAC 2022-01 December 6, 2021" class="- topic/ph "><?FM MARKER [CaseNumber] FAR Case 2018-018?> for a product<?FM MARKER [Why] e.In paragraph (f)(2) introductory text:
i.Removing the term “for an item” and adding “for a product” in its place; and
ii. Removing the term “commercial item” wherever it appears and adding “commercial product or commercial service” in its place;?></ph> or
service treated as a <ph rev="FAC 2022-01 December 6, 2021" class="- topic/ph ">commercial
product or commercial service</ph> under paragraph (f)(1) of this
section but does not meet the definition of a <ph rev="FAC 2022-01 December 6, 2021" class="- topic/ph ">commercial product or commercial
service</ph> as defined at FAR <xref href="2.101.dita#FAR_2_101"
                              base="i1125359"
                              outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly"
                              class="- topic/xref ">2.101</xref> shall
not be exempt from—</p>
                     <ol id="d678e166" class="- topic/ol ">
                        <li class="- topic/li ">
                           <p id="d705e140" class="- topic/p ">
                              <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(i)</ph> Cost accounting standards <ph rev="FAC 2022-01 December 6, 2021" class="- topic/ph "><?FM MARKER [CaseNumber] FAR Case 2018-018?>(see <xref href="Subpart_30.2.dita#FAR_Subpart_30_2"
                                       base="i1087111"
                                       outputclass="fm:Subpart"
                                       class="- topic/xref ">subpart  30.2</xref>); or<?FM MARKER [Why] f. Removing from paragraph (f)(2)(i) “see Subpart 30.2” and adding “see subpart 30.2” in its place; and
g. Removing paragraph (g).?></ph>
                           </p>
                        </li>
                        <li class="- topic/li ">
                           <p id="d705e152" class="- topic/p ">
                              <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(ii)</ph> Certified
cost or pricing data requirements (see <xref href="15.403.dita#FAR_15_403"
                                    base="i1105934"
                                    outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly"
                                    class="- topic/xref ">15.403</xref>).</p>
                        </li>
                     </ol>
                  </li>
               </ol>
            </li>
         </ol>
      </conbody>
